Dates, kick-off times and host cities – get the full schedule for Euro 2020. Twenty-four teams will be playing across 51 matches in 12 cities, starting on Friday June 11. It all ends at Wembley Stadium with the final, which takes place on Sunday July 11. Here’s the full schedule for Euro 2020… Friday June 11 Group A: Turkey vs Italy; Kick-off 10pm (Rome) Also Read: Saturday June 12 Group A: Wales vs Switzerland; Kick-off 4pm (Baku) Group B: Denmark vs Finland; Kick-off 7pm (Copenhagen) Group B: Belgium vs Russia; Kick-off 9pm (St Petersburg) Sunday June 13 Group D: England vs Croatia; Kick-off 4pm (London) Group C: Austria vs North Macedonia; Kick-off 7pm (Bucharest) Group C: Netherlands vs Ukraine; Kick-off 10pm (Amsterdam) Monday June 14 Group D: Scotland vs Czech Republic; Kick-off 4pm (Glasgow) Group E: Poland vs Slovakia; Kick-off 7pm (St Petersburg) Group E: Spain vs Sweden; Kick-off 10pm (Seville) Tuesday June 15 Group F: Hungary vs Portugal; Kick-off 7pm (Budapest) Group F: France vs Germany; Kick-off 10pm (Munich) Wednesday June 16 Group B: Finland vs Russia: Kick-off 4pm (St Petersburg) Group A: Turkey vs Wales: Kick-off 7pm (Baku) Group A: Italy vs Switzerland; Kick-off 10pm (Rome) Thursday June 17 Group C: Ukraine vs North Macedonia; Kick-off 4pm (Bucharest) Group B: Denmark vs Belgium; Kick-off 7pm (Copenhagen) Group C: Netherlands vs Austria; Kick-off 10pm (Amsterdam) Friday June 18 Group E: Sweden vs Slovakia; Kick-off 4pm (St Petersburg) Group D: Croatia vs Czech Republic; Kick-off 7pm (Glasgow) Group D: England vs Scotland; Kick-off 10pm (London) Saturday June 19 Group F: Hungary vs France; Kick-off 4pm (Budapest) Group F: Portugal vs Germany; Kick-off 7pm (Munich) Group E: Spain vs Poland; Kick-off 10pm (Seville) Sunday June 20 Group A: Italy vs Wales; Kick-off 7pm (Rome) Group A: Switzerland vs Turkey; Kick-off 7pm (Baku) Monday June 21 Group C: North Macedonia vs Netherlands; Kick-off 7pm (Amsterdam) Group C: Ukraine vs Austria; Kick-off 7pm (Bucharest) Group B: Russia vs Denmark; Kick-off 10pm (Copenhagen) Group B: Finland vs Belgium; Kick-off 10pm (St Petersburg) Tuesday June 22 Group D: Czech Republic vs England; Kick-off 10pm (London) Group D: Croatia vs Scotland; Kick-off 10pm (Glasgow) Wednesday June 23 Group E: Slovakia vs Spain; Kick-off 7pm (Seville) Group E: Sweden vs Poland; Kick-off 7pm (St Petersburg) Group F: Germany vs Hungary; Kick-off 10pm (Munich) Group F: Portugal vs France; Kick-off 10pm (Budapest) Top two in each group plus four best third-placed teams go through Saturday June 26 Game 1: Group A runners-up vs Group B runners-up; Kick-off 7pm (Amsterdam) Game 2: Group A winners vs Group C runners-up; Kick-off 10pm (London) Sunday June 27 Game 3: Group C winners vs third-placed side from Group D/E/F; Kick-off 7pm (Budapest) Game 4: Group B winners vs third-placed side from Group A/D/E/F; Kick-off 10pm (Seville) Monday June 28 Game 5: Group D runners-up vs Group E runners-up; Kick-off 7pm (Copenhagen) Game 6: Group F winners vs third-placed side from Group A/B/C; Kick-off 10pm (Bucharest) Tuesday June 29 Game 7: Group D winners vs Group F runners-up; Kick-off 7pm (London) Game 8: Group E winners vs third-placed side Group A/B/C/D; Kick-off 10pm (Glasgow) Friday July 2 Quarter-final 1: Game 6 winner vs Game 5 winner; Kick-off 7pm (St Petersburg) Quarter-final 2: Game 4 winner vs Game 2 winner; Kick-off 10pm (Munich) Saturday July 3 Quarter-final 3: Game 3 winner vs Game 1 winner; Kick-off 7pm (Baku) Quarter-final 4: Game 8 winner vs Game 7 winner; Kick-off 10pm (Rome) Euro 2020 Semi-finals Tuesday July 6 Semi-final 1: Quarter-final 2 winner vs Quarter-final 1 winner; Kick-off 10pm (Wembley, London) Wednesday July 7 Semi-final 2: Quarter-final 4 winner vs Quarter-final 3 winner; Kick-off 10pm (Wembley, London) Sunday July 11 Kick-off 10pm (Wembley, London)  Video Of The Day: CAS Rachel Shebesh and athlete Asbel Kiprop share their mental health journeys